<subSubSection id="4B9487FFFFB6A26DB8B4FB12FF09FAB9" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4FB12FF09FAB9" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4FB12FE9DFA85" bold="true" box="[199,334,1267,1293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, a noun in apposition is taken from the “Popoluca de la Sierra” word for mushroom.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B9487FFFFB6A26DB8B4FADBFA5BFAF2" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4FADBFA5BFAF2" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4FADBFE91FADC" bold="true" box="[199,322,1338,1364]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C48EAFF7FFB6A26DB939FADAFDC3FADC" authority="Galán-Sánchez &amp; Álvarez-Padilla, 2022" authorityName="Galán-Sánchez &amp; Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2022" box="[330,528,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Aamunops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noono" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB939FADAFDC3FADC" box="[330,528,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Aamunops noono</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DBA6AFADAFD89FADD" bold="true" box="[537,602,1339,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2AC9B51DFFB6A26DBA6AFADAFD89FADD" box="[537,602,1339,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="C48EAFF7FFB6A26DBB88FADAFB1FFADD" box="[1019,1228,1339,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DBB88FADAFBA2FADD" box="[1019,1137,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Aamunops</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having a short embolus with small denticles on the tip (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBA2EFABEFD7CFAF2" box="[605,687,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
) and by the minute crista on the anterior metatarsi (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBC81FABEFAA8FAF2" box="[1266,1403,1374,1402]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Figs. 65, 66</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B9487FFFFB6A26DB8B4FA63FAEFF88D" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" type="description">
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4FA63FBBCF936" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4FA63FE8AFA14" bold="true" box="[199,345,1410,1436]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB92CFA62FE4AFA15" box="[351,409,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="DC356AD6FFB6A26DB9D4FA62FDC5FA16" box="[423,534,1411,1438]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length 4.00. Cephalothorax 1.70 long, 1.20 wide. Sternum 0.44 long, 0.34 wide. Legs: I 4.44 (1.40) (0.70) (1.10) (0.80) (0.44); II 4.12 (1.22) (0.66) (1.00) (0.80) (0.44); III 3.58 (1.04) (0.50) (0.80) (0.80) (0.44); IV 5.26 (1.46) (0.60) (1.26) (1.38) (0.56). Carapace, sternum, chelicerae, labium, orange (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBD17FA2AFED9F982" captionStart="FIGURES 57–64" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,183,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 57–64. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 57, habitus dorsal view; 58, same lateral view; 59, same ventral view; 60, prosoma anterior; 61, prosoma ventral; 62, pedipalp prolateral view; 63 same ventral view; 64, same retrolateral view. Scale bars: = 1.0 mm (Figs. 57–59), 0.5 mm (Fig. 60), 0.2 mm (Figs. 61–64)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Figs. 57–59, 60</figureCitation>
). Palps and legs light orange; coxae and trochanters lighter (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBBD0FA0EFC25F981" box="[931,1014,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–64" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,183,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 57–64. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 57, habitus dorsal view; 58, same lateral view; 59, same ventral view; 60, prosoma anterior; 61, prosoma ventral; 62, pedipalp prolateral view; 63 same ventral view; 64, same retrolateral view. Scale bars: = 1.0 mm (Figs. 57–59), 0.5 mm (Fig. 60), 0.2 mm (Figs. 61–64)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Endites pale orange, anterior margin lighter (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DB883F9F2FE97F9A6" box="[240,324,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–64" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,183,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 57–64. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 57, habitus dorsal view; 58, same lateral view; 59, same ventral view; 60, prosoma anterior; 61, prosoma ventral; 62, pedipalp prolateral view; 63 same ventral view; 64, same retrolateral view. Scale bars: = 1.0 mm (Figs. 57–59), 0.5 mm (Fig. 60), 0.2 mm (Figs. 61–64)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dorsal pattern light gray, ventral surface whitish (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBB8BF9F2FB51F9A5" box="[1016,1154,1554,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–64" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,183,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 57–64. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 57, habitus dorsal view; 58, same lateral view; 59, same ventral view; 60, prosoma anterior; 61, prosoma ventral; 62, pedipalp prolateral view; 63 same ventral view; 64, same retrolateral view. Scale bars: = 1.0 mm (Figs. 57–59), 0.5 mm (Fig. 60), 0.2 mm (Figs. 61–64)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Figs. 57, 59</figureCitation>
). Anal tubercle and spinnerets pale orange. Crista minute, occupying the most distal portion of the metatarsus ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBD7BF9D6FA43F9DA" box="[1288,1424,1590,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Figs. 65, 66</figureCitation>
). Paired claws with seven teeth (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DB985F9BAFD98F9FE" box="[502,587,1627,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). PLS longer than PMS. Prolateral brush of palpal tibia with six setae (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBD1CF9BAFF64F912" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
); bulb globose, spherical; spermatic duct with a minute, hyaline process (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBB8FF99EFB82F912" box="[1020,1105,1663,1690]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); embolus short, bent, with a wide base (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DB965F942FEA0F935" box="[278,371,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–64" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,183,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 57–64. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 57, habitus dorsal view; 58, same lateral view; 59, same ventral view; 60, prosoma anterior; 61, prosoma ventral; 62, pedipalp prolateral view; 63 same ventral view; 64, same retrolateral view. Scale bars: = 1.0 mm (Figs. 57–59), 0.5 mm (Fig. 60), 0.2 mm (Figs. 61–64)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Figs. 63</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DB90CF942FE4DF936" box="[383,414,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">68</figureCitation>
); tip sharped, with small denticles on the inner margin (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBC7CF942FBB0F936" box="[1039,1123,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,188,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,181,1426]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Aamunops noono sp. n., male. 65, leg I prolateral view; 66, leg II prolateral view; 67, claws prolateral view; 68, embolus tip prolateral and retrolateral view; 69, pedipalp prolateral view. Scale bars: = 0.2 mm (Figs. 65, 66, 69), 0.1 mm (Fig. 67), 0.05 mm (Fig.68). Abbreviations: cr, crista; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4F926FE49F969" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" box="[199,410,1735,1761]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4F926FEC8F969" box="[199,283,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4F90AFAEFF88D" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" box="[199,1340,1770,1797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4F90AFE56F88C" bold="true" box="[199,389,1770,1797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Natural history.</emphasis>
The only known specimen was caught in the leaf litter of a 
<taxonomicName id="C48EAFF7FFB6A26DBC50F90AFB52F88D" box="[1059,1153,1771,1797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DBC50F90AFB52F88D" box="[1059,1153,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest fragment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B9487FFFFB6A26DB8B4F8EFFC8FF8A1" box="[199,860,1806,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0331D474FFB6A26DB8B4F8EFFC8FF8A1" blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,1833]" box="[199,860,1806,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="31FA0866FFB6A26DB8B4F8EFFEB2F8A0" bold="true" box="[199,353,1806,1832]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="DC356AD6FFB6A26DBA13F8EEFD43F8A1" box="[608,656,1807,1833]" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="9BB5C8F1FFB6A26DBA88F8EEFC9DF8A1" box="[763,846,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 83" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1767,1791]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,927,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-344@23.[151,1435,921,1743]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 83. Distribution map of Aamunops species. Black square, A. chimpa sp. n.; white square, A. noono sp. n.; black star, A. misi sp. n.; white star, A. olmeca sp. n.; triangle, O. confuse sp. n.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480084/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="562">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
